name: Lightened Up Green Bean Casserole
description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb fresh green beans, trimmed and cut into bite-sized pieces

  • 2bsp olive oil

  • 1 small onion, finely chopped

  • 2 cloves garlic, minced

  • 8 ounces mushrooms, sliced

  • 2 tbsp whole wheat flour

  • 1 cup low-sodium vegetable broth

  • 1 cup unsweetened almond milk (or any other milk alternative)

  • Salt and pepper to taste

  • 1 tsp dried thyme

  • 1 cup whole grain breadcrumbs

  • 2 tbsp grated Parmesan cheese (optional)

  • Cooking spray

Directions:

  1. Preheat the oven: Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).

  2. Blanch the green beans: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add the green beans and cook for 3-4 minutes, then immediately transfer them to a bowl of ice water to stop the cooking process. Drain and set aside.

  3. Make the mushroom sauce:

    • In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add chopped onions and garlic, sautéing until softened.

    • Add sliced mushrooms and cook until they release their moisture and become golden brown.

    • Sprinkle flour over the mushroom mixture and stir well to coat. Cook for 1-2 minutes to remove the raw flour taste.

    • Slowly whisk in the vegetable broth and almond milk. Stir continuously until the mixture thickens.

    • Season with salt, pepper, and dried thyme. Allow the sauce to simmer for a few minutes until it reaches a creamy consistency.

  4. Assemble the casserole:

    • Add the blanched green beans to the mushroom sauce, stirring until well coated.

    • Transfer the mixture to a lightly greased baking dish.

  5. Prepare the topping:

    • In a small bowl, mix the whole grain breadcrumbs with grated Parmesan cheese (if using).

    • Sprinkle the breadcrumb mixture evenly over the green bean mixture.

  6. Bake:

    • Bake in oven for 20-25 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the casserole is bubbling around the edges.

  7. Serve:

    • Allow the casserole to cool for a few minutes before serving.

    • Enjoy your healthier green bean casserole!

name: Roasted Brussels Sprouts with Balsamic Glaze
description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb Brussels sprouts, trimmed and halved

  • 2 tbsp olive oil

  • Salt and black pepper to taste

  • 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar

  • 1 tbsp honey or maple syrup (optional, for sweetness)

  • 1-2 cloves garlic, minced (optional, for added flavor)

  • 2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley (for garnish, optional)

Directions:

  1. Preheat the Oven:

    Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).

  2. Prepare Brussels Sprouts:

    • Trim the ends of the Brussels sprouts and cut them in half.

    • Place them in a large bowl.

  3. Seasoning:

    • Drizzle olive oil over the Brussels sprouts, ensuring they are evenly coated.

    • Season with salt and black pepper to taste. Add minced garlic if desired.

  4. Roast Brussels Sprouts:

    • Spread the Brussels sprouts in a single layer on a baking sheet.

    • Roast in oven for 20-25 minutes or until they are golden brown and crispy on the edges. Shake or stir them halfway through to ensure even cooking.

  5. Prepare Balsamic Glaze:

    • While the Brussels sprouts are roasting, prepare the balsamic glaze.

    • In a small saucepan, heat balsamic vinegar over medium heat.

    • Optional: add honey or maple syrup for sweetness. Simmer for 5-7 minutes or until the vinegar has reduced by half and has a syrupy consistency.

  6. Combine and Glaze:

    • Once the Brussels sprouts are done roasting, transfer them to a serving bowl.

    • Drizzle the balsamic glaze over the roasted Brussels sprouts and toss them to coat evenly.

  7. Garnish and Serve:

    • Optionally, garnish with chopped fresh parsley for a burst of freshness.

  8. Serve Warm:

    • Serve the roasted Brussels sprouts with balsamic glaze immediately while warm.

name: Thanksgiving Kale Salad with Roasted Butternut Squash
description:
Ingredients:

For the Salad:

  • 1 bunch kale, stems removed and leaves thinly sliced

  • 2 cups butternut squash, peeled and diced into bite-sized pieces

  • 1/2 cup pumpkin seeds (pepitas), toasted

  • 1/3 cup dried cranberries

  • 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled (optional)

  • Salt and black pepper to taste

For the Dressing:

  • 3 tbsp olive oil

  • 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar

  • 1 tbsp maple syrup or honey

  • 1 tsp Dijon mustard

  • Salt and black pepper to taste

Directions:

  1. Roast Butternut Squash:

    • Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).

    • Toss the diced butternut squash with a bit of olive oil, salt, and pepper.

    • Spread the squash on a baking sheet in a single layer and roast for 20-25 minutes or until tender and golden brown. Allow it to cool.

  2. Prepare Kale:

    • In a large bowl, massage the kale with a bit of olive oil for a few minutes until it becomes tender and dark green.

  3. Assemble the Salad:

    • Add the roasted butternut squash, toasted pumpkin seeds, dried cranberries, and crumbled feta cheese (optional) to the massaged kale.

  4. Prepare the Dressing:

    • In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, balsamic vinegar, maple syrup or honey, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.

  5. Dress the Salad:

    • Pour the dressing over the salad and toss everything together until well coated.

  6. Chill (Optional):

    • If time allows, let the salad chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.

  7. Serve:

    • Serve the kale salad in a large bowl or on a platter, and sprinkle additional pumpkin seeds and cranberries on top for garnish if desired.

name: Sweet Potato Casserole with Pecan Topping
description:
Ingredients:

For the Sweet Potato Filling:

  • 4 medium sweet potatoes, peeled and cubed

  • 2 tbsp coconut oil or olive oil

  • 1 egg

  • 1/4 cup pure maple syrup or honey

  • 1 tsp ground cinnamon

  • 1/2 tsp nutmeg

  • 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk (or any milk alternative)

  • 1 tsp vanilla extract

  • Pinch of salt

For the Pecan Topping:

  • 1 cup pecans, chopped

  • 1/4 cup whole wheat flour (or other flour alternative)

  • 2 tbsp coconut oil, melted

  • 2 tbsp pure maple syrup or honey

  • 1/2 tsp cinnamon

  • Pinch of salt

Directions:

  • Preheat the Oven:

    Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).

  • Cook Sweet Potatoes:

    • Place the sweet potato cubes in a large pot of water and bring to a boil.

    • Cook until the sweet potatoes are tender, about 15-20 minutes.

    • Drain the sweet potatoes and transfer them to a large mixing bowl.

  • Mash Sweet Potatoes:

    • Mash the sweet potatoes with a potato masher or fork until smooth.

  • Add Ingredients to the Filling:

    • Add beaten egg, coconut oil, maple syrup (or honey), cinnamon, nutmeg, almond milk, vanilla extract, and a pinch of salt to the mashed sweet potatoes. Mix well until combined.

  • Prepare the Pecan Topping:

    • In a separate bowl, combine chopped pecans, whole wheat flour, melted coconut oil, maple syrup (or honey), cinnamon, and a pinch of salt.

    • Mix until the pecans are evenly coated.

  • Assemble the Casserole:

    • Transfer the sweet potato mixture to a baking dish, spreading it evenly.

  • Add Pecan Topping:

    • Sprinkle the pecan topping evenly over the sweet potato layer.

  • Bake:

    • Bake in oven for 25-30 minutes, or until the pecan topping is golden brown.

  • Serve:

    • Allow the casserole to cool for a few minutes before serving.

name: Meal Prep Breakfast Burritos
description:
Ingredients:

  • 6 large tortillas (whole wheat or low-carb options for extra fiber)

  • 6 large eggs

  • 1 cup egg whites

  • 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar, Monterey Jack, Mozzarella, or your favorite variety)

  • 1 lb ground turkey sausage

  • 1/2 tsp salt

  • 1/2 tsp black pepper

  • 1/2 tsp paprika

  • 1/4 tsp garlic powder

  • Cooking spray or 1 tsp olive oil

Directions:

  1. Cook the Turkey Sausage

    • Heat a skillet over medium heat. Spray with cooking spray.

    • Add turkey sausage and cook until browned and fully cooked, about 8–10 minutes.

    • Season with smoked paprika and garlic powder. Set aside.

  2. Prepare the Eggs

    • In a mixing bowl, whisk together eggs and egg whites with salt and pepper.

    • In the same skillet (wipe clean if needed), lightly spray with cooking spray and pour in the egg mixture.

    • Cook on low-medium heat, stirring gently to create soft scrambled eggs. Remove from heat.

    • Combine the eggs, turkey sausage, and cheese in a bowl. Stir to combine.

  3. Assemble the Burritos

    • Lay out each tortilla.

    • Add a portion of the mixture (~3/4-1 cup) to the center of each tortilla.

  4. Wrap the Burritos

    • Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling, then roll tightly from bottom to top to form a burrito.

    • Repeat with all tortillas.

    • Optional: Briefly brown the seam-side of each burrito in the skillet to help seal it shut.

  5. Store for Meal Prep

    • Fridge: Wrap each burrito in foil or parchment paper and store in an airtight container. Refrigerate for up to 5 days.

    • Freezer: Wrap burritos individually in plastic wrap, then foil, and place them in a freezer bag. Freeze for up to 3 months.

  6. Reheat Before Eating

    • From the fridge: Microwave for 1–1:30 minutes, flipping halfway.

    • From the freezer: Microwave for 3–4 minutes, flipping halfway.

These burritos are great on their own or dipped in salsa. You can pair them with fresh fruit for a complete breakfast. Need extra calories? Swap egg whites for whole eggs, add more cheese, or mix in veggies like sautéed bell peppers or spinach.

Enjoy your delicious, protein-packed breakfast burritos!

Ingredients:

  • 12 ounces rotisserie (or leftover chicken) chicken, shredded

  • 3 TBSP non-fat Greek yogurt

  • 3 TBSP salsa

  • 1 tsp cumin

  • 1 tsp paprika

  • 1 tsp garlic powder

  • salt and pepper to taste

  • 8 small corn tortillas

  • 1 cup cheddar cheese, grated

Optional Toppings

  • pickled onions

  • cilantro

  • cotija cheese

  • lime wedges

  • sour cream or Greek yogurt

Directions:

  1. Preheat the oven to 425°F. Lightly spray a baking sheet with olive oil to coat or line with parchment paper.

  2. Prepare the filling: In a mixing bowl, combine the shredded chicken, Greek yogurt, salsa, cumin, paprika, garlic powder, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir until everything is well combined.

  3. Warm the tortillas so they don’t break while rolling:

    • Oven: 1–2 minutes

    • Microwave: 45–60 seconds (between damp paper towels)

  4. Assemble the tacos:

    • Distribute the creamy salsa chicken onto each tortilla.

    • Top with shredded cheddar.

    • Fold the tortilla over and place it on the prepared baking sheet.

    • Repeat with remaining tortillas.

  5. Brush or spray the outsides of the folded tortillas with olive oil and top with remaining cheese if desired.

  6. Bake for 12–15 minutes, until the tacos are crispy and golden brown.

  7. Serve immediately with pickled onions, sour cream or Greek yogurt, cotija cheese, fresh cilantro, and lime wedges for spritzing. Also pairs great with this Easy Pico.
